[1]
Date: Wed, 16 Dec 1998 21:13:14 +0530
From: Prativa Pandey <pandey@mos.com.np>

The four rabies deaths in western Nepal and one reported earlier in
the year from Kathmandu all have one thing in common -- the patients
received the nervous tissue Semple vaccine that the government
provides, [but did not receive] Rabies Immune Globulin (Human or
Equine).
What I would like to point out is that, besides considering
vaccine failure or inadequate treatment in these cases, one must
also consider whether deaths are due to the known neurologic
complications from the Semple vaccine. The nervous tissue vaccines
are known to cause neuroparalytic reactions ranging from 1:200 to
1:1200 vaccine recipients and 25%of these reactions are reported to be
fatal.
Some of these deaths could easily have been due to vaccine-related
complications and not due to rabies.
--
Prativa Pandey, M.D.
Medical Director
The CIWEC Clinic Travel Medicine Center
Kathmandu, Nepal
e-mail: pandey@mos.com.np
[No doubt. - Mod CHC]
