Date: Wed, 16 Dec 1998 17:58:21 -0800
From: Yvonne_McHugh@cc.chiron.com

RabAvert/Rabipur rabies vaccine for use in humans
----------------------------------------------------
I am a devoted reader of ProMED as well as the medical education liaison
for Chiron Corporation's RabAvert(TM) tissue culture rabies vaccine for use
in humans (pre- and post-exposure prophylaxis) in the US. The same
vaccine, but known as Rabipur(R) is sold and distributed in 30 countries
throughout the world, including Nepal, where the four cases of human rabies
were just reported. It is the most used tissue culture rabies vaccine for
use in humans in the world (over HDCV vaccines). The abbreviation used to
describe this vaccine is "PCEC" (purified chick embryo cell).
Rabipur/RabAvert is produced by Chiron in Marburg, Germany.

RabAvert/Rabipur is an excellent rabies vaccine for use in humans in that
it has a high potency with very low reactogenicity (pre- and post-exposure
use), and no type III hypersentivity reactions reported.

As I am sure you read the CDC's MMWR, RabAvert is discussed in the January
16, 1998/Vol.47/No.1 issue; and will be integral to the "Rabies Prevention
- US: Recommendations of the ACIP" which will be published in the MMWR late
1998 or early 1999.

--
Yvonne McHugh, Ph.D.
Scientific Affairs
Chiron Corporation
Emeryville, CA USA
